<tr><td bgcolor="#363636">
<a name="bloodstained_tunic"></a>
<font color="#FFFFFF" face="Arial">
<strong>Bloodstained Tunic - AC 13</strong>
<font size=-1>(<a href="/prices/item/bloodstained_tunic.shtml">View Going Price</a>)</font><BR>
Slot: <a href="/armour/chest.shtml">Chest</a><BR>
Weight: 6.5 - All Races<BR>
Classes: <a href="/bard/armour/chest.shtml">BRD</a>, <a href="/cleric/armour/chest.shtml">CLR</a>, <a href="/paladin/armour/chest.shtml">PAL</a>, <a href="/ranger/armour/chest.shtml">RNG</a>, <a href="/rogue/armour/chest.shtml">ROG</a>, <a href="/shadow_knight/armour/chest.shtml">SHD</a>, <a href="/shaman/armour/chest.shtml">SHM</a>, <a href="/warrior/armour/chest.shtml">WAR</a><BR>
<font color=red>
(Magic) <BR>
(AGI +4) (WIS +4) </font>
<BR>
Rare drop from the Undead Knight in Unrest.<BR>
<BR>
Avg. Price Overall: 324pp (88 quotes)<BR>
Last 30 Days: 200pp (1 quotes)<BR>

</td></tr>
</table>
<center><a href="/comments/item_comment.shtml?ID=85">Post a Comment</a>
</center><BR>
<center>
 [ <a href="/armour/individual/bloodstained_tunic.shtml?ID=85&page=1"> 1 </a> ] [ <a href="/armour/individual/bloodstained_tunic.shtml?ID=85&page=2"> 2 </a> ] [ <a href="/armour/individual/bloodstained_tunic.shtml?ID=85&page=3"> 3 </a> ]</center>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Aababba Habib-Vallon Zek</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-01-10 21:31:00</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>This tunic is very nice, displays as red banded armor for the chest.  The Undead Knight of Unrest spawns in the tower in place of the festering hag sometimes.  While the spawn rate is not that slow for that particular area, he happens to spawn probably one out of fifty times, if that.  The hag is around level 27, while the Knight is about level 29-30 and likes to harm touch you before the fight starts, which is always fun for everyone.  He also casts spells as a SK of his level so be careful, although I've never seen it with a pet.  If your high enough to kill him, I doubt anything else will train on you, although if you get low enough life things wont hesitate to.  The tunic, as I said is very nice, and the BS mantle is always a great booby prize.  He's frequently camped however, but all in all, a good item for a hard kill.<BR>
<BR>
I killed a barbarian to get mine, screw the bunnie servers.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
